</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[707,1194,193,1094]" pageId="5">
<keyLead pageId="5">
3. Body notably slender (
<figureCitation box="[975,1112,193,215]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[175,215,1614,1633]" captionTargetBox="[171,1152,193,1591]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[170,1153,192,1591]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 8–15. 8) Trichohippopsis suturalis, holotype female, dorsal habitus; 9–12) Trichohippopsis rufula: 9) Dorsal habitus, female from MZSP collection; 10) Holotype, lateral habitus; 11) Holotype, dorsal habitus; 12) Holotype drawing by Breuning (1958); 13) T. rufula sensu Breuning (1962); 14) Aprosopus buquetii, holotype, dorsal habitus; 15) Aprosopus gilmouri, holotype, dorsal habitus (true color changed due to the slide from which it was copied). Photographs in Figs. 10–11 by Camille Locatelli; photographs in Figs. 14–15 by Gérard L. Tavakilian." pageId="5">Figs. 9–11, 15</figureCitation>
); pubescence forming longitudinal bands on pronotum and elytra (excluding sutural band) .............. 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[707,1194,193,1094]" pageId="5">
<keyLead pageId="5">
3′. Body more robust (
<figureCitation box="[958,1058,282,303]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,237,1662,1681]" captionTargetBox="[179,1185,193,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[179,1187,192,1639]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–7. 1–4) Trichohippopsis birai, holotype female: 1) Dorsal habitus; 2) Ventral habitus; 3) Lateral habitus; 4) Head, frontal view; 5) Trichohippopsis exilis, paratype female, dorsal habitus; 6) Trichohippopsis magna, holotype female, dorsal habitus; 7) Trichohippopsis vestita, holotype female, dorsal habitus." pageId="5">Figs. 1, 6</figureCitation>
); pubescence not forming longitudinal bands on pronotum and elytra (excluding sutural band).............5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[707,1194,193,1094]" pageId="5">
<materialsCitation country="Brazil" location="Goias" pageId="5" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Goias">
<keyLead pageId="5">
4. Prothorax about 1.2 times longer than wide; elytral apex curved at outer angle (
<figureCitation box="[1082,1181,395,417]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[175,215,1614,1633]" captionTargetBox="[171,1152,193,1591]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[170,1153,192,1591]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 8–15. 8) Trichohippopsis suturalis, holotype female, dorsal habitus; 9–12) Trichohippopsis rufula: 9) Dorsal habitus, female from MZSP collection; 10) Holotype, lateral habitus; 11) Holotype, dorsal habitus; 12) Holotype drawing by Breuning (1958); 13) T. rufula sensu Breuning (1962); 14) Aprosopus buquetii, holotype, dorsal habitus; 15) Aprosopus gilmouri, holotype, dorsal habitus (true color changed due to the slide from which it was copied). Photographs in Figs. 10–11 by Camille Locatelli; photographs in Figs. 14–15 by Gérard L. Tavakilian." pageId="5">Figs. 9–11</figureCitation>
